---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro'
---

<Base
  title="Privacy"
  description="What Queer Omaha collects, why, and who it's shared with."
>
  <article class="legal-page">
    <wa-card class="legal-card">
      <h2 slot="header">
        <wa-icon name="shield-halved" variant="solid" aria-hidden="true"></wa-icon>
        Privacy
      </h2>

      <p>
        Queer Omaha is a volunteer-run, community-maintained directory. There
        are no accounts and no logins — this page covers everything we
        collect.
      </p>

      <h3>What we collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics.</strong> We use PostHog to see which pages and
          listings get used, in cookieless mode: no cookies, no persistent
          device ID, and IP addresses aren't logged.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Suggestion Box submissions.</strong> The message you type
          into the footer's "Suggest a place to add" form, sent via Netlify
          Forms.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form submissions.</strong> The email and message
          you send via <a href="/contact">/contact</a>, also via Netlify
          Forms.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Why</h3>
      <p>
        To understand which categories and listings people actually use, and
        to receive suggestions and messages from the community.
      </p>

      <h3>Who we share it with</h3>
      <p>
        PostHog Inc. (analytics) and Netlify, Inc. (form handling and
        hosting) — that's it. We don't sell data or share it with anyone
        else.
      </p>

      <h3>How long we keep it</h3>
      <p>
        Analytics events are kept per PostHog's standard retention.
        Suggestion Box and contact submissions are kept until they're
        reviewed and actioned.
      </p>

      <h3>Questions</h3>
      <p>
        Email <a href="mailto:privacy@queeromaha.net">privacy@queeromaha.net</a>
        or use the <a href="/contact">contact form</a>.
      </p>

      <p>
        <a class="back-link" href="/friends">
          <wa-icon name="arrow-left" variant="solid" aria-hidden="true"></wa-icon>
          Back to the directory
        </a>
      </p>
    </wa-card>
  </article>
</Base>
